TITLE: Scoping Marten Session to a Specific Tenant (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to scope a Marten session to a specific tenant and query data within that tenant. It creates a query session for the "tenant1" tenant and then queries for User documents. Because the session is scoped to "tenant1", the query will only return data associated with that tenant. It relies on DocumentStore.QuerySession(tenantId) to create the scoped session.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/docs/documents/multi-tenancy.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
// When you query for data from the "tenant1" tenant,
// you only get data for that tenant
using (var query = store.QuerySession("tenant1"))
{
    query.Query<User>()
        .Select(x => x.UserName)
        .ToList()
        .ShouldHaveTheSameElementsAs("Bill", "Lindsey");
}
```

