TITLE: Chaining Patch Operations - C#
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to chain multiple patch operations together, in this case `Set` and `Increment`.  The operations are executed atomically within a single database transaction.  It uses `SaveChangesAsync()` to commit the changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/docs/documents/partial-updates-patching.md#_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
[Fact]
public async Task able_to_chain_patch_operations()
{
    var target = Target.Random(true);
    target.Number = 5;

    theSession.Store(target);
    await theSession.SaveChangesAsync();

    theSession.Patch<Target>(target.Id)
        .Set(x => x.Number, 10)
        .Increment(x => x.Number, 10);
    await theSession.SaveChangesAsync();

    using (var query = theStore.QuerySession())
    {
        query.Load<Target>(target.Id).Number.ShouldBe(20);
    }
}
```

