TITLE: Ejecting a Document from Session
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to remove a document from the identity map and unit of work tracking within a session using IDocumentSession.Eject. It stores two Target documents, ejects one, and verifies that the ejected document is no longer in the identity map or persisted after SaveChangesAsync.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/docs/documents/sessions.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
var target1 = Target.Random();
var target2 = Target.Random();

using (var session = theStore.IdentitySession())
{
    session.Store(target1, target2);

    // Both documents are in the identity map
    session.Load<Target>(target1.Id).ShouldBeSameAs(target1);
    session.Load<Target>(target2.Id).ShouldBeSameAs(target2);

    // Eject the 2nd document
    session.Eject(target2);

    // Now that 2nd document is no longer in the identity map
    session.Load<Target>(target2.Id).ShouldBeNull();

    await session.SaveChangesAsync();
}

using (var session = theStore.QuerySession())
{
    // The 2nd document was ejected before the session
    // was saved, so it was never persisted
    session.Load<Target>(target2.Id).ShouldBeNull();
}
```

