TITLE: Querying for Multiple Results as JSON Array - C#
DESCRIPTION: This C# code demonstrates how to create a compiled query (`FindJsonOrderedUsersByUsername`) that returns multiple user results as a JSON array. It implements `ICompiledListQuery<User>` and defines the `QueryIs()` method to filter users by `FirstName` and order them by `UserName`.  The implicit `ToJsonArray()` call is not present in this snippet but is part of how this compiled query is used.
