TITLE: Conditional Schema Creation using IF NOT EXISTS
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates creating a new schema named 'inventory' only if it does not already exist. It uses an IF NOT EXISTS statement within a PL/pgSQL block to check for the schema's existence in the information_schema.schemata view before executing the CREATE SCHEMA statement. This prevents errors if the schema already exists.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/documentation/documentation/postgres/if_statements.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: PL/pgSQL
CODE:
```
DO $$
BEGIN
    IF NOT EXISTS(
        SELECT schema_name
          FROM information_schema.schemata
          WHERE schema_name = 'inventory'
      )
    THEN
      EXECUTE 'CREATE SCHEMA inventory';
    END IF;
END
$$;
```

