TITLE: Using QueryStatistics with Compiled Queries - C#
DESCRIPTION: This C# code demonstrates how to use `QueryStatistics` with compiled queries in Marten to get the total number of rows matching a query. The `TargetsInOrder` class implements `ICompiledListQuery<Target>` and exposes a public `QueryStatistics` property. The query orders targets by `Id`, skips a certain number of records, and takes a specified page size.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/docs/documents/querying/compiled-queries.md#_snippet_17

