TITLE: Custom IRetryPolicy Implementation in Marten (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates a custom implementation of the `IRetryPolicy` interface in Marten for handling failing database operations. It retries a preconfigured number of times and includes an optional predicate based on the thrown exception type. It requires a dependency on Npgsql and uses asynchronous operations for retries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/documentation/documentation/documents/advanced/retrypolicy.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
public class SampleRetryPolicy : IRetryPolicy
{
    private readonly int _maxRetries;
    private readonly Func<Exception, bool> _exceptionPredicate;

    public SampleRetryPolicy(int maxRetries = 3, Func<Exception, bool> exceptionPredicate = null)
    {
        _maxRetries = maxRetries;
        _exceptionPredicate = exceptionPredicate ?? (_ => true);
    }

    public async Task<bool> ShouldRetry(Exception ex, int attempt, CancellationToken token)
    {
        if (attempt > _maxRetries)
        {
            return false;
        }

        return _exceptionPredicate(ex);
    }
}

```

