TITLE: Configuring Soft Deletes with Partitioning
DESCRIPTION: This C# code demonstrates how to configure Marten to use PostgreSQL table partitioning for soft-deleted documents.  It shows how to opt into partitioning for a single document type, with an index, and for all soft-deleted documents.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/docs/documents/deletes.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
var store = DocumentStore.For(opts =>
{
    opts.Connection("some connection string");

    // Opt into partitioning for one document type
    opts.Schema.For<User>().SoftDeletedWithPartitioning();

    // Opt into partitioning and and index for one document type
    opts.Schema.For<User>().SoftDeletedWithPartitioningAndIndex();

    // Opt into partitioning for all soft-deleted documents
    opts.Policies.AllDocumentsSoftDeletedWithPartitioning();
});
```

