TITLE: Creating a Schema Conditionally
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a schema in PostgreSQL only if it doesn't already exist. It uses a PL/pgSQL block with an IF statement to check for the existence of the schema in the `information_schema.schemata` catalog. If the schema doesn't exist, it executes a `CREATE SCHEMA` command.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/docs/postgres/if-statements.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
DO $$
BEGIN
    IF NOT EXISTS(
        SELECT schema_name
          FROM information_schema.schemata
          WHERE schema_name = 'inventory'
      )
    THEN
      EXECUTE 'CREATE SCHEMA inventory';
    END IF;
END
$$;
```

