TITLE: Querying to AsyncEnumerable with Marten in C#
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the `ToAsyncEnumerable()` extension method in Marten to process query results as an `IAsyncEnumerable<T>`. It fetches a set of `Target` objects, iterates through them asynchronously, and verifies that the expected number of objects were retrieved. The code requires Marten and xUnit for testing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/docs/documents/querying/linq/async-enumerable.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
[Fact]
public async Task query_to_async_enumerable()
{
    var targets = Target.GenerateRandomData(20).ToArray();
    await theStore.BulkInsertAsync(targets);

    var ids = new List<Guid>();

    var results = theSession.Query<Target>()
        .ToAsyncEnumerable();

    await foreach (var target in results)
    {
        ids.Add(target.Id);
    }

    ids.Count.ShouldBe(20);
    foreach (var target in targets)
    {
        ids.ShouldContain(target.Id);
    }
}
```

