TITLE: Using Live Transformed Events in C#
DESCRIPTION: This sample demonstrates how to query for live transformed events using the `TransformTo<T>` extension method. This allows you to retrieve the transformed view document directly from the event store without needing to pre-calculate it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/marten/blob/master/documentation/documentation/events/projections/index.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
// SAMPLE: using_live_transformed_events
using var host = Host.CreateDefaultBuilder()
    .ConfigureServices(services =>
    {
        services.AddMarten(opts =>
        {
            opts.Projections.Add<MonsterDefeatedTransform>(ProjectionLifecycle.Inline);
        });
    }).Build();

using (var scope = host.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var store = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<IEventStore>();

    var streamId = Guid.NewGuid();
    await using (var session = store.OpenSession())
    {
        session.Events.Append(streamId, new MonsterSlayed("Troll", "Bob"));
        await session.SaveChangesAsync();
    }

    await using (var querySession = store.QuerySession())
    {
        // Look up the transformed view from the underlying event stream
        var defeated = await querySession
            .Events
            .QueryStream(streamId)
            .TransformTo<MonsterDefeated>(streamId);
    }
}
// ENDSAMPLE
```

